Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Input sequences of single-particle indices", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8874562566990304`*^9, 3.887456258704954*^9}, {
  3.8883150838482122`*^9, 
  3.8883150934469776`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"449e637c-f7d0-4628-9d06-\
e4ea8c1dfce7"],

Cell["\<\
Loading of the 480 (240) input sequences of single particle indices, \
corresponding to composite Feynman diagrams of conjoint type with a two-body \
vertex and two non-identical (identical) one-body interaction vertices. \
Contributions with non-identical vertices are twice the ones generated by two \
identical vertices, as the former do not possess any vertex permutation \
symmetry and hence have multiplicity corresponding to the one generated by \
internal single-particle index exchanges in the two-body vertex.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJxTTMoPSmViYGAQAWIQ/fjUjej4H28cu54lJIDokiTzrB4gHaIeBabl+mOP
